description: Testing rules — agent must run tests, not only suggest them
globs: ["tests/**", "**/*.test.ts", "**/*.spec.ts", "scripts/smoke*.ts", "server/**", "app/**"]
alwaysApply: true
---
Vitest for unit/integration, Playwright for e2e. Add/update tests with any business-logic change.

## Agent obligation (required before marking work done)
- **Run tests yourself** in the terminal — do not tell the user to test unless blocked (missing secrets, manual OAuth, etc.).
- Minimum for feature work: `npm run db:validate`, relevant smoke script (`npm run smoke:e2e`, `npm run smoke:booking`), and typecheck/lint on touched paths.
- **After every sprint or UI feature:** run `npm run build` and confirm every **new or changed route** compiles (no client bundle pulling `pg`, `dns`, `fs`, or `@/lib/db/prisma`). Client components (`"use client"`) must not import server-only modules — split into `lib/*` (pure) vs `server/*` (Prisma/DB).
- If Stripe/Resend keys are missing, still run DB smoke + document what could not be exercised.
- Report exact commands run and pass/fail in the handoff summary.

## Coverage priorities
Authorization paths and critical flows: onboarding, booking→job, crew completion, payments (manual + Stripe webhook when configured).

Run `scripts/ai/validate.sh` when the full suite is green; otherwise run the closest applicable smoke scripts and fix failures.
